His plea for help turned down, a compromised spy and his family are presumably killed on duty. But when Dr. Quest visits a cave in New Mexico, he finds that Ezekiel Rage—and his anger towards the government—is very alive. Though this is Rage's first chronological appearance in the series, it is his second production-wise, having aired after Rage's Burning Wheel.
